	Descending Binary Trees











A rooted binary plane tree on n vertices starts with a root vertex r. Every vertex in the tree either has (1) no children, (2) a left child, (3) a right child. or (4) both a left and right child. Here are all of  the rooted binary plane trees for n=1,2,3.






